page.title: 02Wareham Forest
page.content:
{Wareham Forest}was planted after World War One by the{Forestry Commission.} The forest is divided into compartments, and many different types of trees are planted. The trees are grown for timber. Some of the trees planted are :_{Bishop {Pine, Corsican Pine, Scots Pine, {Maritime Pine, Lodgepole Pine, Radiata {Pine, Oak and European Larch.}
New trees are planted with seeds from {North America}and from this country. New forests are planted to blend with the landscape, and the Forestry Commission are improving existing forests.
